title: ice_age_(movie)
body:
An American franchise of animated movies revolving around animals of the titular period of time.
Five theatrical films have been released in the series: Ice Age in 2002, Ice Age: The Meltdown in 2006, Ice Age: Dawn of the Dinosaurs in 2009, Ice Age: Continental Drift in 2012, and Ice Age: Collision Course in 2016. As of April 2016, the franchise had generated $6 billion in revenue, making it one of the highest-grossing media franchises of all time.

title: mahjong_soul

Japanese name: Jantama

Mahjong Soul is a Chinese browser-based online free-to-play tabletop gacha game about riichi [[mahjong]] created by Cat Food Studio and [[Yostar]]. It was released in June 2018 in China and April 2019 in Japan and worldwide, also for Android and iOS devices. It features charming anime-style characters that can be unlocked with in-game currency. title: ibuki_suika
body:
The "Little Pandemonium". Final boss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Immaterial and Missing Power]] and later a recurring playable character. 

Suika claims to be the only [[oni]] living above the ground in [[Gensokyo]] - the rest of her kind have lived underground for centuries. She is always found [[drunk]]en, carrying a bottomless [[gourd]] of [[sake]], and is an avid lover of parties. She has the power to control the density of any given object. She is explicitly based on the oni king Shuten-douji.

She is friends with [[Yakumo Yukari]], [[Hoshiguma Yuugi]] (both were once part of the "Four Devas of the Mountains") and [[Hakurei Reimu]], whose shrine also serves as her sometimes home. She and [[Ibaraki Kasen]] appear to have a slightly strained relationship, given Kasen's breaking rank with the other Gensokyo Sages, but the two remain mostly friendly to each other.

h4. Appearance
* !asset #24058201

Her hair color varies between [[blonde hair|blonde]], [[brown hair|brown]], or [[orange hair|orange]] but is almost always [[very long hair|very long]] and [[low-tied long hair|tied near the bottom]] with [[sidelocks]]. Her eyes also [[yellow eyes|vary]] [[brown eyes|between]] [[orange eyes|those]] colors or [[red eyes|red]]. She wears a [[red bow]] in her [[hair bow|hair]] and a [[purple bow]] [[horn bow|on]] [[brown horns]]. Her outfit is a [[sleeveless shirt|sleeveless]] [[white shirt]], a [[red bowtie]], a [[ribbon-trimmed skirt|ribbon-trimmed]] [[purple skirt]], [[white socks]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[shoes]]. She sometimes has her [[wrist cuffs]] or normal [[cuffs]] with a [[cube]], [[orb]], and [[pyramid (geometry)|]] attached on [[chain]]s. 

h4. See also

* [[List of Touhou characters]]

h4. External links

* "Touhou Wiki: Suika Ibuki":http://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Suika_Ibuki

title: tube_dress
body:
A [[strapless]] close-fitting casual [[dress]]. Essentially a [[tube top]] extended to dress length. Tube dresses generally reach from just past the hips to knee length, and they tend to fit snugly around the legs like a [[pencil skirt]] or [[pencil dress]].

As this tag implies [[strapless]], do not use this tag if the dress has shoulder straps or a [[halterneck]]; in such cases, [[pencil dress]] should be used instead.

h4.Correct examples
* !post #6300054
* !post #5301484
* !post #7150488: A tube dress worn with a [[grey jacket]]

h4.Incorrect examples
* !post #4084150: [[Pencil dress]] held up by [[halterneck]]
* !post #3962732: Pencil dress held up by shoulder straps such as [[spaghetti strap]]s
* !post #2633071: Pencil dress that is [[sleeveless dress|sleeveless]]
* !post #5352352: [[Off-shoulder dress]]

h4. See also

* [[pencil dress]]
* [[pencil skirt]]
* [[strapless dress]]

title: hugh's_sister_(pokemon)
body:
[[Hugh (pokemon)|]]'s unnamed younger sister from [[pokemon_bw2|Pokémon BW2]]. She takes her appearance from the [[twins_(pokemon)|Twin]] NPC Trainer.
She was gifted a [[Purrloin]] by her late grandfather, but it was stolen by a member of the [[Shadow Triad]] a few years prior to the main story's events. This event would lead her brother to embark on a journey to recover it, but it had already evolved into a [[Liepard]] with no recollection of its previous life by the time he found it.

title: helluva_boss
body: [b]Helluva Boss[/b] is an animated web series set in the same universe of [[Hazbin Hotel]]. The series follows the misadventures of the [b]Immediate Murder Professionals[/b], or I.M.P., an assassination group that kills humans on Earth on behalf of their clients from Hell. Lead by the demon [[blitzo (helluva boss)|Blitzo]] along with his employees, husband and wife duo, Moxxie and [[millie (helluva boss)|Millie Knolastname]] and his adopted daughter [[loona (helluva boss)|Loona]], I.M.P. tries they best to complete their mission while dealing with other problems.

title: kirby_64
body:
A direct sequel to [[Kirby's Dream Land 3]], despite the name not making that very clear.

One day, the peaceful world of [[Ripple Star]] is attacked by [[Dark Matter (kirby)|]], which quickly begins to cover the planet in darkness. In a last-ditch effort, the [[Ripple Star Queen]] sends a fairy named [[Ribbon (kirby)|]] away to protect the treasured Crystal. Ribbon manages to escape, but not before having the Crystal shattered in an ambush from Dark Matter.

Ribbon crashes down on [[Pop Star]], right on top of [[Kirby]] as he was watching the night sky. Sharing her problems with him, the carefeee hero gladly decides to help out. The two then set out on another adventure, recruiting a few friends along the way!

One of the game's main mechanics is Kirby's ability to combine [[Copy Ability|Copy Abilities]] together called [[Power Combo (kirby)|]], giving him unique combat abilities, such as "wielding a fire sword":[/posts/7554641] or "maneuvering a giant drill":[/posts/334573]

title: sylveon
body:
[[Pokemon|Pokémon]] #700 in the National PokéDex. 

It evolves from [[Eevee]] when leveled up knowing a Fairy-type move and having at least two Affection hearts. The method of getting Affection has changed from game to game, since Generation 6. 

Sylveon is a quadruped, mammalian Pokémon covered primarily in pale cream-colored fur with pinkish feet, ears, and tail. There are two [[bow]]s on its body, one on its left ear and one around its neck, from which two feelers adorn it. The bows are pale cream with pinkish centers, while the feelers are pale cream with pinkish and blue tips. It has short, slender legs and small paws with three visible toes on each foot. Its eyes are blue with white pupils and no visible sclera.

The shiny variant keeps the cream-colored fur, but replaces the pink fur with a minty blue color. The ribbons end with a pinkish color, and its eyes are red instead of blue. 

Japanese name: [b]Nymphia[/b]

Type: Fairy
Ability: Cute Charm (Hidden: Pixilate)
Height: 100 cm / 3'3"
Weight: 23.5 kg / 51.8 lbs

"Bulbapedia page":[https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Sylveon_(Pok%C3%A9mon)]

Prior Pokémon: [[Aurorus]]
Next Pokémon: [[Hawlucha]]

title: zoroark
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #571 in the National PokéDex, a Dark type Pokémon.
Zoroark is a bipedal, gray-brown, fox-like Pokémon with crimson and black accents. It has a pointed snout and ears with red insides. It also has some red rimming its eyes and mouth. It has a large, red, voluminous mane with black tips, which somewhat resembles a ponytail, as a teal bangle down its length separates a mass of the mane from the lower portion. It has a black ruff on its upper body, pointed at the shoulders from which its arms extend.

The first [[pokemon|Pokémon]] to be revealed to appear in the fifth main installment of the Pokémon franchise. The fox-like Pokémon is a Dark-type that evolves from [[Zorua]]. It uses its Illusion ability [[disguised_zoroark|to disguise itself as other Pokémon]]. A Zoroark took the central role in the thirteenth [[pokemon_(anime)|Pokémon movie]].

It evolves from [[Zorua]].

Type: Dark
Ability: Illusion
Height: 160 cm / 5'3"
Weight: 81.1 kg / 178.8 lbs

Japanese Name: [b]Zoroark[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Zorua]]
Next Pokémon: [[Minccino]]

title: kite_shield
body: A type of tall medieval European [[shield]] with a distinctive pointed almond shape (hence also sometimes called an [i]almond shield[/i]). Commonly associated with the Battle of Hastings (1066) due to its ubiquity on the Bayeux tapestry. Not to be confused with a [i]heater shield[/i], which is the classic smaller point-at-the-bottom shield shape commonly seen in heraldry, early issues of [i][[Captain America]][/i], and United States Interstate Highway System signage.

title: scutum
body: The stereotypical [[shield]] of the ancient Roman [[legionnaire|legionary]], tall and usually rectangular, with a distinctive outward vertical curvature. The [i]scutum[/i] appeared among Romans in the fourth century BC, its precise origins unknown, and largely replaced the earlier [i]clipeus[/i], a circular shield adopted from the classical Greeks. Also often sported (in a wildly exaggerated form) by members of the [[Adeptus Astartes]] of [i][[warhammer 40k|Warhammer 40,000]], as part of their general faux-Roman styling.

title: planted_shield
body: When a [[shield]] is placed with its lower edge touching, or even driven into, the ground, converting it into a makeshift [[wall]]. For obvious reasons, this is more often done with large shields, such as medieval [[kite shield]]s or ancient Roman [i][[scutum|scuta]][/i].

title: olympus_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Lostbelt No. 5: Interstellar Mountainous City, Olympus[/b]
[quote]
Four Lostbelts have been cut away from Proper Human History.
As they break through the great ocean that remained unchanged since the Age of Gods, the Chaldeans see before them a Tree of Emptiness that stretches out into space, along with a giant floating city towering majestically over all, symbolizing the absolute rule of the gods.

Olympus...

A throne for the superior deities and a great Interstellar city so massive that even the vast sea of the skies is no obstacle to it.

The final battle for humanity versus the gods...and Master versus Crypter begins here, at the epicenter of the fifth Lostbelt.
[/quote]
The second part of the fifth Lostbelt in [[Fate/Grand Order]], set in the city of Olympus and supervised by the Crypter [[Kirschtaria Wodime]]. title: atlantis_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Lostbelt No. 5: Ancient Ocean of the Dreadnought Gods, Atlantis[/b]
[quote]
Kirschtaria, the leader of the Crypters, controls a Lostbelt rich in giant relics left by the gods.
Its residents are strong, godsfearing people who stand firm even in the face of the Demonic Beasts which threaten the region.
It is a place dominated by a civilization that once stood at the height of supremacy, but is now little more than a shadow of its former glory.
All that remains finds itself adrift in a vast ocean.
That ocean's name: Atlantis. This world, in Proper Human History, is said to be one of the lost ancient civilizations.

A grueling conflict where both sides leave nothing in reserve ensues in the fifth and largest Lostbelt yet. It is said that this day will see a god brought down...
But will that foretelling bear fruit or wither on the vine?
[/quote]
The first part of the fifth Lostbelt in [[Fate/Grand Order]], set in the Atlantic Ocean and supervised by the Crypter [[Kirschtaria Wodime]]. title: yugakshetra_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Lostbelt No. 4: Saṃsāra of Genesis and Terminus, Yugakshetra[/b]
[quote]
In this journey to cut down the Fantasy Trees, the battles in the Lostbelts grow more intense. To prepare for the inevitable confrontation with Kirschtaria, Chaldea journeys to the fourth Lostbelt in search of supplies and reinforcements.

The Indian Lostbelt.
Not a hint of devastation is seen in this land, where the people pray to their god each day and live humble lives. Where the Chinese Lostbelt was governed by the laws of men, this Lostbelt is a pure land ruled by the laws of its god.

What awaits the Master of Chaldea in this world trapped in perpetual Saṃsāra meant to purge all Evils?
[/quote]

title: s_i_n_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Lostbelt No. 3: The Synchronized Intellect Nation, S I N[/b]
[quote]
Shortly after Chaldea settles in at their new base, an assassin strikes, attempting to poison members of their group.
In a desperate bid to save the lives of the assassin's would-be victims, Chaldea makes its way to the third Lostbelt, hoping to find an antidote.

They arrive in a land of eternal peace, brought on by the end of all conflict between nations.
This land knows no struggle, no tragedy, no fragility... a truly idyllic world. Time passes gently, and the people live comfortable lives. And yet...
[/quote]
The third Lostbelt in [[Fate/Grand Order]], set in [[China]] and supervised by the Crypter [[Akuta Hinako]]. In this universe, the first emperor of China [[Shi Huang Di (fate)|]] managed to obtain immortality, allowing for his eternal rule.

title: anastasia_(lostbelt)_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Lostbelt No. 1: Permafrost Empire, Anastasia[/b]
[quote]
On that fateful day, the future was wiped clean. Invaders from another world have swept aside human history, bringing everything back to the beginning.
Our achievements were undone, and Proper Human History was no longer even a part of the past.
The observatory is frozen, and the world itself split into seven Lostbelts.
And now...
After three months of silence, the last remaining humans surface from the Sea of Void. They journey through a frigid, icy world, shut out from history.
April, 2018... The battle to reclaim the world and its history begins.
[/quote]
The first Lostbelt in [[Fate/Grand Order]], set in [[Russia]] and supervised by the Crypter [[Kadoc Zemlupus]]. Here, an [[asteroid]] hit the planet in 1570 and caused an ice age, resulting in most of humanity to go extinct; however [[Ivan the Terrible (fate)|]] was able to save his country by transforming the remaining humans (including himself) into Yaga by merging them with magical beasts.

Released on the Japanese server on April 4, 2018 and on the NA server on March 27, 2020.

title: salem_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Pseudo-Singularity IV: The Forbidden Advent Garden, Salem[/b]
[quote]
It happened suddenly...without warning.

It snuffed out all the light in the land, and it enveloped an entire town under the cover of night. Such a phenomenon could only be described as...darkness. The enormous, malicious magical energy emanating from within the darkness bears a strong resemblance to the shadow of one of the Demon Gods who attempted the Incineration of Humanity.

What will become of this heretical land when the causes of this evil are eradicated?
[/quote]
The fourth pseudo-singularity in [[Fate/Grand Order]], set in the town of Salem in the year 1692 during the Salem witch trials. After the events of the [[Solomon (singularity) (fate/grand order)|Solomon singularity]], several [[demon pillar (fate)|]]s escaped and created subcategory singularities, resulting in the creation of Salem (among others). [spoiler]The demon pillar [[Raum (fate)|]] created a recreation of historical Salem and [[Abigail Williams (fate)|]], placing them in a time loop where he kept reiterating the same events in an attempt to summon the outer god Sut-Typhon.[/spoiler]

Released on the Japanese server on November 29, 2017 and on the NA server on December 2, 2019. It was adapted into a manga by [[Oomori Aoi]].

Upon release of Salem (and the other pseudo-singularities), the true name of several new servants was initially hidden; however official Fate/Grand Order media would later forego keeping their true names hidden in promotional materials. Their aliases are listed below, but their true names are used on Danbooru for tagging.

title: agartha_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Pseudo-Singularity II: Subterranean World of Folklore, Agartha[/b]
[quote]
The Demon God Pillars who were seperated from the 72 Demon Gods each found their purpose.
These scraps of the Beast scattered around the globe, forming Pseudo-Singularities—stains in the fabric of human history.
Central Asia, the 21st century.
In a time and place where no major conflicts were recorded, a Singularity has appeared underground, and a Demon God Pillar's influence is suspected.
The next Pseudo-Singularity operation will take place in the vast subterranean cavern Agartha.
[/quote]
The second pseudo-singularity in [[Fate/Grand Order]], set in a massive underground world beneath the Asian continent in the year 2000. After the events of the [[Solomon (singularity) (fate/grand order)|Solomon singularity]], several [[demon pillar (fate)|]]s escaped and created subcategory singularities, resulting in the creation of Agartha (among others).

Released on the Japanese server on June 29, 2017 and on the NA server on June 21, 2019. It was adapted into a manga by [[Takenaka Hideo]].

Upon release of Agartha (and the other pseudo-singularities), the true name of several new servants was initially hidden; however official Fate/Grand Order media would later forego keeping their true names hidden in promotional materials. title: camelot_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Sixth Singularity: Divine Realm of the Round Table, Camelot[/b]
[quote]
The setting of the sixth Grand Order is the year 1273, a holy land where many gather to worship.
Gallant knights battle for the restoration of humanity in a kingdom scarred by a history that should not exist!
[/quote]

The sixth singularity in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. Set in the year 1273 in [[Jerusalem]], it was originally registered as a variation of the Ninth Crusade that was successful in reaching Jerusalem; however due to the summoning of the [[Lion King (Lancer) (Fate)|Lion King]] it instead became home to a recreation of the city of Camelot from Arthurian legend, with the Chaldean forces arriving 6 months later.

Released on the Japanese server on July 25, 2016 and on the NA server on June 28, 2018. It was adapted into 2 anime films, [i]Wandering; Agateram[/i] and [i]Paladin; Agateram[/i].

body:
[b]Third Singularity: Sealed Ends of the Four Seas, Okeanos[/b]
[quote]
The third Grand Order is set in 1573.
This is the Age of Exploration where many pirates give their lives for endless treasures.
In this sealed sea, Okeanos, due to the Incineration of Humanity, legendary pirates will risk everything for the greatest treasure, the Holy Grail.
[/quote]
The third singularity in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. It's set in the year 1573 in an endless ocean, after [[Francis Drake (fate)|]] went on a voyage and encountered [[Poseidon (mythology)|]] in Atlantis, where she defeated him and acquired his [[holy grail (fate)|]]. Due to another holy grail being inserted in the era as part of the plot to incinerate humanity, the energy of the two competed together resulting in the endless ocean.

title: fuyuki_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Singularity F: Flame Contaminated City, Fuyuki[/b]
[quote]
Disaster strikes Chaldea, the Security Organization for the Preservation of Humanity.
A lone Master is thrown into Fuyuki during the year 2004, where a Holy Grail War is raging.
The journey to reclaim human history begins in a desolate, burning city.
[/quote]
The tutorial singularity in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. Technically the first singularity, but isn't numbered as such as it serves as a prologue, instead being known as Singularity F. It's set in the year 2004 in the Japanese town of Fuyuki, where a [[Fate/stay night|certain holy grail war]] has ended in disaster. It was adapted into the film [i][[Fate/Grand Order: First Order]][/i].

body:
A trope in which a [[light bulb]] appears over a character's head, usually after an extended period of [[thinking]]. It is a cartoony way of showing an [[idea]] switching on.

The light bulb should appear above the characters head and not be a background detail. Do not confuse for [[spoken light bulb]]s or a [[light_bulb_hair_ornament]].

title: emerl_(sonic)
body:
An ancient [[humanoid robot]] that appears in [[Sonic Battle]]. Its original name was "Gizoid", but the name Emerl was given because of its ability to absorb [[chaos_emerald|Chaos Emeralds]].
Having been first researched upon by [[Gerald Robotnik]], It was discovered and subsequently abandoned by [[Dr. Eggman]]. Afterwards, Emerl begins traveling alongside [[sonic_the_hedgehog|Sonic]] and each of his friends, and grows gradually smarter and stronger by imitating their abilities and absorbing Emeralds. However, gaining power over one of Eggman's weapons forces Sonic to fight Emerl himself.

A different robot called [[Gemerl]] was created from Emerl's data, following its eventual destruction.
H4. External links
* "Sonic Fandom Wiki":https://sonic.fandom.com/wiki/Emerl

title: shinjou_akane
body:
The second female protagonist of [[SSSS.Gridman]].

[spoiler]She is revealed to be the series' secondary antagonist, working with [[Alexis Kerib]] by designing [[kaiju|kaiju]] sculptures that Alexis brings to life. Akane is shown to be sociopathic as she easily holds petty grudges against others, even for simple accidents.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]In episode 6, it is revealed that Akane is the creator of the city and uses the kaiju to shape it to her liking by killing off anyone she doesn't like and resetting it afterwards.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]In the finale episode, it is revealed that Akane is actually [[shinjou_akane_(real)|a person]] from [[real life]] world who was abducted by Alexis so he could feed on her negative energy.[/spoiler]

title: creeper
body:
A [[monster]] from the game [[Minecraft]]. It is one of the most dangerous hostile mobs in the game. Spawns in the Overworld on light level of zero. Its only attack is to [[explosion|explode]], fatally damaging the player, and destroying nearby blocks. This, combined with its nearly silent footsteps and its only making its trademark "Tsss" (or "シュー" as it's known in Japanese) when it is about to explode—has given it a notorious reputation for taking players completely by surprise.

Amongst the Japanese community it has earned the nickname "匠" or "たくみ (Takumi)", which translates to "Craftsman." Being one of the most memorable and original mobs in the game, it has become a kind of mascot for Minecraft.

It is the primary source of gunpowder. A creeper surviving a lightning strike will turn into the more powerful [[charged creeper]]. If killed by a [[skeleton (minecraft)|]] or [[stray (minecraft)|]], it will drop a [[music disc (minecraft)|]].

h4.See also
* [[creeparka]]
* [[creeper (tool)]] (a type of mechanic's tool)

title: hanuman_vs._7_ultraman
body:
a.k.a. "[i]The 6 Ultra Brothers vs. the Monster Army[/i]" in Japan.

A theatrical movie from the [[Ultra Series]], released in 1974 in Thailand, and in 1979 in Japan.

This movie is a international co-production between [[Tsuburaya Productions]] and Chaiyo Productions, a company from Thailand.

Nowadays, it is notorious for instigating the court battle between Tsuburaya and Chaiyo, over the international licensing rights for the Ultra Series, specifically, the first six entries, ([[Ultra Q]], [[Ultraman (1st series)|]], [[Ultraseven (series)|]], [[Kaette kita Ultraman|Return of Ultraman]], [[Ultraman Ace (series)|]], and [[Ultraman Tarou (series)|]]) of the franchise.

title: madou_meihou-sou_no_kousatsu
body:
[b]A Study in the Dubious Meihou-sou[/b]

[quote]The story begins when a new minute Singularity is detected...

Structured differently than any yet seen, the Singularity contains myriad locations and symbols from various time periods all in one place.
It's almost like like being in a movie.
In this world, created from the bitter frustration of a filmmaker who left a movie unfinished, completing the production is of the greatest importance.

Amid a flurry of speculation about the film's ending, one can only wonder how this story will conclude when the mystery is finally laid to rest.
[/quote]

An event in [[Fate/Grand Order]] guest-written by Madoi Ban which was later adapted into a novel illustrated by [[Honjou Raita]]. In it, Chaldea visits a singularity where they must finish the production of a murder-mystery themed film. [[Murasaki Shikibu (fate)|]] ends up penning the draft for the story, but the ending (and who the mastermind is) remains up in the air until production is concluded. This event also introduces a [[Bartholomew Roberts (fate)|stray servant]] who can't remember his true name, who goes by his character's name of Salazar.

h4. Characters
* Ryuu Tan ([[Yagyuu Munenori (fate)|]])
* Miguel Ángel Cortés ([[James Moriarty (Archer) (fate)|]])

title: bartholomew_roberts_(fate)
body:
Rider-class Servant in [[Fate/Grand Order]].

A Welsh pirate who raided ships around the Americas and West Africa, and considered to be the most successful pirate of the Golden Age of Piracy as determined by the number of captured ships. He was killed by a grapeshot cannon during a naval battle and had his corpse thrown overboard so he could be buried at sea.

He is also known as [b]Black Bart[/b] or [b]Salazar[/b].

title: john_hammond
body: Dr. John Alfred Hammond was the CEO of InGen and creator of [[Jurassic Park]]. He founded the company InGen and the Hammond Foundation. He had at least one daughter, two grandchildren (Tim and Lex Murphy), a sister (as Hammond's nephew has the surname of Ludlow, not Hammond) and a nephew, Peter Ludlow.

title: paw_pose
body:
A hand pose imitating [[paws]].
Stereotypically arms in front ; elbows bent up; hands close to chest (sometimes face), palm outward and closed in loose.

Often with the onomatopoeia [[nyan]] (にゃん) near, in imitation of a cat's meow.

h4. Example
* !post #3801607

h4. Not to be confused with

* [[claw pose]] (fingers curled)
* [[ghost pose]] (hands limp)
* [[zombie pose]] (arms straight, hands limp)

h4. See also

* [[Tag group:Gestures]]

title: ian_malcolm
body: Dr. Ian Malcolm is a mathematician who specializes in a branch of mathematics known as "Chaos Theory". Malcolm is the tritagonist of the [[Jurassic Park]] franchise, serving as the tritagonist of Jurassic Park, the main protagonist of The Lost World: Jurassic Park, one of the three unseen overarching protagonists of [[Jurassic World]], a minor character in Jurassic World: Fallen Kingdom, and one of the three overarching protagonists of Jurassic World: Dominion. Malcolm appears in both novels by Michael Crichton. Malcolm serves as the mouthpiece of Crichton, who called Malcolm the "ironic commentator" on the action. In the movies, Malcolm is portrayed by Jeff Goldblum. Malcolm also appeared in most other Jurassic media like comics, video games and toy lines.

title: jurassic_world
body:
The 4th instalment in the [[Jurassic Park]] film franchise, released in 2015.

It revolves around a successor to the original park opening for business 22 years after the events of the first film. Again, chaos ensues when a hybrid [[dinosaur]], the [i]Indominus rex[/i], escapes its enclosure and terrorises the park.

title: ultra_galaxy_mega_dai-kaijuu_battle
body:
The 22nd and 23rd installments of the long-running [[Ultra Series]], and the start of the [[Ultra Galaxy (series)|]] sub-series. It adapts the concept of the [i]Dai-Kaijuu Battle: ULTRA MONSTERS[/i] cardass arcade game, itself the start of the Dai-Kaijuu Battle sub-series (covering the arcade games and ports, manga, and this show), and features an original plot.

Unlike previous entries, this show does not focus on Ultramen, instead focusing on [[kaiju]] battling each other, akin to [[Pokemon]] (itself inspired by [[Ultraseven (series)|]]'s Capsule Monsters). It follows the ZAP SPACY team, and in particular, [[Reimon]], a Reionic, who can summon kaiju to fight with using his Battlenizer.

h4. See also

* [[Dai-Kaijuu Battle Ultra Ginga Densetsu The Movie]]

h4.External links

* "Wikipedia article":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultra_Galaxy_Mega_Monster_Battle

title: ultraman_tiga_(series)
body:
The 12th installment of the long-running [[Ultra Series]], and the first entry in the Heisei era.

It introduces the concept of a "type-changing" Ultraman, as in the titular [[ultraman tiga|Ultra]] character changes forms/colors, depending on the battle.

[spoiler]
The show also serves as a 30th anniversary celebration of the franchise, as seen in Episode 49, aptly titled, "The Ultra Star".
[/spoiler]

In 2002, the show was dubbed in English by [[4Kids|4Kids Entertainment]], making it one of the few Ultra series dubbed in the US. The dub however, proved to be unpopular with fans, ultimately causing 4Kids to drop the show halfway through, instead opting to release an uncut, subtitled version of the series on DVD, courtesy of [[Funimation]].

h4. See also

* [[Ultraman Tiga: The Final Odyssey]]
* [[Global Unlimited Task Squad uniform]]

h4. External links

* Officially streaming on YouTube thru the TokuSHOUTsu channel (episode 1 only): "Subbed":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q2UEHi0hPSE]*
* "Wikipedia article":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultraman_Tiga
<tn>Original theme song "Take Me Higher" not included.</tn>

title: mach_rider
body:
A motorcycle-focused racing game released for the [[famicom|NES]] on 1985. 

In the year 2112, the [[Mach Rider (character)|]] rides from sector to sector to search for survivors while gunning down the alien invaders riding vehicles known as Quadrunners. 

An [[arcade_cabinet|arcade]] version, [i]Vs. Mach Rider[/i], released a few months prior. It's namesake is based on a [[toy]] [[Nintendo]] released back in 1972.[tn]"[1]":[http://famicomblog.blogspot.com/2014/08/the-original-mach-rider.html][/tn]

title: magical_mirai_miku_(2024)
body:
The 2024 [[Magical Mirai (vocaloid)|]] version of [[Hatsune Miku]], designed by [[tama (songe)|]].

This year's theme is "Fan Fun Trip" and features a travel motif.

Miku has [[asymmetrical bangs]] and a [[gradient hair]] ending in [[blonde hair|yellow]]. She wears a [[white hat|white]] [[beret]] and [[white jacket|white]] [[cropped jacket]] with the imagery of a suitcase. She has a [[yellow skirt|yellow]] [[layered skirt]] consisting of a [[belt]], and [[white shorts]] [[shorts_under_skirt|underneath]]. She carries a [[flag]] and a [[shoulder bag]] [[suitcase]] with [[microphone]]s attached.

title: nakiri_ayame_(hololive_summer_2019)
body:

body:
A 2D platforming game and sequel to [i][[Donkey Kong Country]][/i], released on the [[Super Nintendo]] in 1995 by Rare Ltd.

title: kerbal_space_program
body:
A popular space flight and construction simulator famed for its physics engine and scientific accuracy. You the player are in charge of a space program on the planet Kerbin, populated by a species of large-headed green people known as Kerbals. The goals are the construction and launching of spacecraft, exploration, and development of the solar system, or just blowing shit up and ebing a general failure (which is what the majority of the playerbase does). Has a large modding community with all kinds of historical and sci-fi content.

h4.External links

* "Official page":[https://kerbalspaceprogram.com/en/]
other_names: カーバルスペースプログラム

title: alice_(black_souls)
body:
Major character in [[Black Souls]] and Black Souls 2. Based on [[Alice in Wonderland]].

Can appear as several variations including Daughter Alice, Little Sister Alice, and Mother Alice in Black Souls 2.

[spoilers]
She's modeled after the real [[Alice Liddell (black souls)|]], who was into a relationship with Lewis Carroll until her father exiled the latter. Years later, Carroll became disgusted upon finding Alice's youthful beauty was gone and wished to go back to the old days, resulting in him being spirited away by Mary Sue and becoming Grimm.

Alice is a role played by The Crawling One a.k.a. [[Nyarlathotep]].
[[Daughter Alice (black souls)|]] is a role played by [[bandersnatch_(black_souls)| Bandersnatch ]]
[[Sister Alice (black souls)|]] is a role played by [[jubjub_(black_souls) | JubJub]]
[[Mother Alice (black souls)|]] is a role played by [[jabberwock_(black_souls)  | Jabberwock]]
[[Doll Alice (black souls)|]] is the Grand Guignol 
[/spoilers]

title: robin_(honkai:_star_rail)
body:
A playable character in [[Honkai: Star Rail]] and the little sister of [[Sunday (Honkai: Star Rail)|]]. Voiced by [[Nazuka Kaori]] in Japanese. 

She is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[light blue hair]], [[head wings]], [[halo]], [[blue eyes]], and [[medium breasts]]. Her default outfit consists of a [[strapless dress|strapless]] [[two-tone dress]] set in [[white dress|white]] and [[purple dress|purple]], [[white gloves|white]] [[elbow gloves]], [[feather boa]], and [[purple footwear|purple]] [[high heels]].

h4. Costumes

* !post #7691440: Splash art
* !post #8513172: [[Robin (Brilliant Youth) (Honkai: Star Rail)|Brilliant Youth]]

h4. Profile
[expand]
"There's a saying — the more demanding the diner, the stronger the skills of the chef... but no matter what others say, I'll always be demanding more from myself."

A Halovian singer born in Penacony and rose to cosmic fame. An elegant and demure young lady. This time, she has been invited home by The Family to grace everyone with a song at the Charmony Festival.

She can use the power of Harmony to broadcast her music, manifesting "resonance" among not only her fans but all manner of lifeforms.
[/expand]

title: setsuna_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Setsuna[/b] (セツナ) is a playable character in [[Fire Emblem Fates]].

One of [[Hinoka (fire emblem)|]]'s retainers. She is quiet and shows up at unexpected places at unexpected times. She's extremely clumsy, but shameless, making her unpersonable. Prone to spacing out in her leisure time, and silently shoots things down to pass the time.

She is voiced by Ishikawa Ayana in the Japanese version.

body:

Depending on context, such as if the circles are dot-size and are used as texture rather than pattern print, [[ben-day dots]] should be used instead. Not to be confused with [[halftone]].

title: in-universe_location
body:
A recognizable location in a game, anime, or other fictional universe. 

It should be recognizable either through landmarks, architecture, terrain, and if it's the [[interior]] of a house or other structure, through floor, walls, furniture, or some other notable characteristic.

h4. Examples

* !post #8168903: [tn]Geffen, a town from [[Ragnarok Online]][/tn]
* !post #3204592: [tn]Labyrinth Zone, a level from [[Sonic the Hedgehog (classic)|]][/tn]
* !post #8426946: [tn]Neo Star Stage 1, from [[Kirby 64]][/tn]

Other examples include: towns, levels, stages, dungeons, outdoor locations or hub areas in video games; the school, or the student council room in a slice-of-life anime; the tournament arena in an action manga; etc.

h4. See also

* [[real world location]]

title: jewelpet_(creature)
body:
Titular species of magical [[creature]] from the [[Jewelpet (series)|]] series. They are magical pets who reside in Jewel Land and pair up with humans to find magical jewels.

Jewelpets are considered to be popular [[chibikemo]] characters, as they usually walk on two legs by default, though they can also take on a quadruped form if they wish.

title: shirogane_noel_(1st_costume)
body:
The default costume of [[hololive]]'s [[Shirogane Noel]].

It consists of a [[short dress|short]], [[collared dress|collared]], [[pleated dress|pleated]] white-and-blue [[armored dress]] (although sometimes it's depicted as a separate shirt and skirt) with a [[puffy sleeves]] and a noticeably large [[cleavage cutout]] to the right hand side (described by Noel as a "ventilation"), a small white [[tabard]] or [[pelvic curtain]], a white [[waist cape]] a [[brown belt|brown]] [[leather belt]] with a [[belt pouch]] and [[black thighhighs]]. She also wears an [[armor]] consisting of a [[single pauldron]], a [[chest guard]] held with a [[chest harness]] and a [[chest strap]], [[vambraces]], [[black gloves|black]] [[fingerless gloves]] and [[greaves]]. In her hair, she has dark grey [[tiara]] with gold accents.
She also carries a [[mace]] on her waist.

h4. Appearance

* !post #3589683: Profile
* !post #3803098: Merchandise

title: one_side_up
body: A variation of [[two side up]] in which some locks of hair are tied up on one side while the rest hangs normally. Neither length or volume of the tied up hair nor that of the other free-flowing hair matters for tagging purposes, only that the remaining hair falls down loosely. Not to be confused with [[side ponytail]], where the majority of one's hair—save for [[sidelocks]]—is pulled up into a ponytail that leaves no hair falling loosely. If the hair is not tied up but just sticking out on its own, tag as [[side ahoge]]. h5. Examples * !post #6414776: short hair, short side up * !post #6426051: short hair, long side up * !post #7775296: medium hair, short side up * !post #6373249: medium hair, long side up * !post #6431000: long hair, short side up * !post #6511326: long hair, long side up * !post #7158018: [[single side bun]] h5. Not [[one side up]] * !post #7237036: [[side ponytail]] * !post #7612721: [[low side ponytail]]

title: suica
body:
[b]Super Urban Intelligent Card[/b], a type of smart card used by [[East Japan Railway Company]] for fares in Kantou region. The name is a play on the word "[i]suika[/i]", ie. watermelon, and also the combination of the ideophone "[i]sui sui[/i]", ie. "moving smoothly", and "card". Thanks to the good recognisability of the name, it's well suited for puns.

title: final_fantasy
body:
A popular, long-running role-playing game series by [[Square Enix]].

Final Fantasy first appeared in 1987 in reaction to Enix's [[Dragon Quest]]. Contrarily to what is often said, while Square wasn't doing great at the time, the first game wasn't made as a last ditch attempt to save the company. It did end up being a great commercial success and as a result, subsequent titles (each set in a different universe) were published ever since.

When tagging the first game, use [[Final Fantasy I]].

title: belarus_(hetalia)
body:

body:

title: realified
body:
A type of character design based on applying "real life logic" where a [[Pokemon_(creature)|pokemon]], [[Pal_(creature)|Pal]], [[Digimon_(creature)|digimon]], etc is drawn as the thing or creature they were based on. Distinct from simply being drawn well or [[realism]] in that it is about applying "real world logic" to the design. Though the distinction can be blurry espcially when dealing with designs that already closely resemble what they are based on, eg, pokemon that very closely look like a real life animal with little change. A good indicator of this can be a character design being changed to be more like the real life counterpart, such as a bipedal character based on a quadrupedal creature being drawn walking on all fours like the real life creature. As opposed to just adding more detail, eg visible strands of fur on something that was already furry but not that detailed.

h6. Examples
* !post #6246371
* !post #624590
* !post #8387525
* !post #3793739

h6. Realified vs just detailed/well drawn
* !post #682593: Realified. Proportions of a real turtle.
* !post #7529050: Detailed but not made to look like an actual turtle.

title: matsudaira_nobutsuna_(fate)
body:
Supporting character in [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s chapter [i][[Ooku (fate/grand order)|Tokugawa Restoration Labyrinth, Ooku]][/i]. A concept that opposed [[Kama_(fate)|]]'s power was imbued in his soul and a spell was engraved in his body to transform his organs into [[hanafuda]] cards, which made him incessantly cough blood. He acted as a double agent, serving Kama while scattering the cards throughout the labyrinth, aiding Chaldea with their power. Nobutsuna later sacrifices himself and a blade emerges from his body for [[yagyuu_munenori_(fate)|Yagyuu]] to wield, gaining advantage over Kama.

He also appears briefly in the opening animation for Fate/Samurai Remnant, but nowhere else in the game.

[B]Character Design[/b]: [[Furumi Showichi]]

[spoiler]He turns out to be the true Servant [[Solomon (fate)|Solomon]], who uses the wish gained by winning the Holy Grail War to incarnate himself as a human in order to experience all that he hadn't in life. He uses his final Noble Phantasm, Ars Nova, to erase himself from existence and give the heroes a fighting chance at defeating Goetia at the final battle in the Solomon singularity.[/spoiler]

title: king_k._rool
body:
Main antagonist of the [i][[Donkey Kong (series)|]][/i] series, introduced in the original [i][[Donkey Kong Country]][/i]. He is the leader of the Kremlings, a race of [[crocodilian]]s that constantly antagonize [[Donkey Kong]] and the Kong Family. 

His most distinctive physical trait is his single [[bloodshot_eyes|bloodshot eye]]. In his default [b]King[/b] persona he dons a gold [[crown]], a [[red cape]] with a [[brooch]], and golden [[bracer]]s. However he is known to adopt other personas such as [b]Kaptain K. Rool[/b] where he wears a [[pirate]] look with a [[pirate hat]] carrying a [[blunderbuss]], [b]Baron K. Roolenstein[/b] where he adopts a [[mad scientist]], [[frankenstein's_monster|frankenstein]]-like look with a [[lab coat]], and [b]King Krusha K. Rool[/b] where he takes on the look of a boxer with [[boxing gloves]] and a [[championship belt]]. 

His name is a pun on "cruel". Colloquially it is commonly pronounced as "King Kay Rool" in English speaking countries as well as officially in [i][[Super Smash Bros.]] Ultimate[/i]. The television show usually pronounced his name as "King Kuh Rool". In Japanese it's pronounced as "King Cruel".

h4. Official Art
* !post #3217762
other_names: キング"クラッシャー"クルール

title: donkey_kong_country
body:
[quote][i][tn]"The king of swing, the thrilla gorilla, the prime primate; it's Donkey Kong! But this is not your father's Donkey Kong! Although he is a relative of the classic arcade character, Country's Donkey Kong is a totally new character, with a new look, new moves, and a new attitude."[/tn][/i][/quote][tn]—Donkey Kong Country Instruction Booklet, page 12[/tn]

A 2D platforming game developed by Rare Ltd, released on the [[Super Nintendo]] in 1994. It stars [[Donkey Kong]] and his buddy [[Diddy Kong]] in their quest to trek the entirety of Donkey Kong Island in order to recover their stolen [[banana]]s from an antagonistic [[crocodilian]] race known as the Kremlings. 

This title rebooted the [i][[Donkey Kong_(series)|]][/i] franchise, changing Donkey Kong from a villain to a hero, giving him a new design, an entirely new setting, and a new cast of supporting characters and enemies.

title: kannazuki_no_miko
body:
[b]Kannazuki no Miko[/b] (lit. [i][[miko|Priestesses]] of the Godless Month[/i]) is a manga series created by the duo [[Kaishaku]]. The series was serialized in fourteen chapters by [i]Kadokawa Shoten[/i] and in [i]Shounen Ace[/i] in 2004 and 2005, and collected in two bound volumes. The series was adapted as an anime television series broadcast in 12 episodes on [i]TNK[/i] between October and December 2004. A drama CD was released on November 25, 2004 by [i]Geneon[/i] based on the anime version.

The series centers on the [[yuri]] relationship of the two main characters, [[kurusugawa_himeko|Himeko]] and [[himemiya_chikane|Chikane]], with elements of [[magical girl]] and [[mecha]] themes helping to carry the plot. An anime series that includes several characters similar to those of [i]Kannazuki no Miko[/i] called [i][[Kyoushirou to Towa no Sora]][/i] aired in Japan between January and March 2007.

Because it was one of the first yuri romances in an anime that was played as a straight romance, it's become iconic for yuri romance, especially its ED artwork, featuring the memetic [[miko embrace]].  (The pose is essentially synonymous with yuri.)

The manga and anime were originally released in English under the original Japanese title by Tokyopop and Geneon USA respectively. After Geneon USA's shutdown, distribution rights for the anime were transferred to Sentai Filmworks, who now distribute the series under the English title [b]Destiny of the Shrine Maiden[/b].

title: dark_elf
body:
An [[Elf]] sub-type who are said to be troublesome to others or affiliate themselves with evil and/or dark sides. In some works, they are treated as a separate but related species of elves and are not necessarily evil.

Dark elf appearances vary from depiction to depiction. Many, such as those inspired by [[Dungeons & Dragons]] tend to have [[colored skin]] in various tones of [[blue skin|blue]], [[grey skin|grey]], or [[purple skin| purple]]. Others like the [[Dark Eldar]] from [[Warhammer 40k]] tend to have extremely [[pale skin|pale]] or [[white skin]]. Typical dark elves in many Japanese copyrights instead just have [[dark skin]].

This tag can also be applied for elves from copyrights where they have none of the above yet it is their title as a character.

h4. See also

* [[elf]]
* [[Tag Group:Legendary Creatures]]

Named [b]Niyah[/b] in the Japanese version.

A member of the main cast. She is a Gormotti Driver whose Blade is [[dromarch (xenoblade)|Byakko]] (Dromarch).

She has [[short hair|short]] [[grey hair]] with [[blunt bangs]], [[yellow eyes]] and [[cat ears]]. She wears a [[yellow bodysuit]] with [[white gloves]]. She usually has [[small breasts]] or a [[flat chest]], depending on the artist.

She also has [[facial mark]]s (a short white cat-like stripe from her forehead and each cheek), but artists frequently forget them.

She wields [[chakram]]s in battle.

[spoiler]Later revealed to be a Flesh Eater Blade. See [[nia (blade) (xenoblade)|Nia (Blade)]].[/spoiler] The DLC also gives her a swimsuit costume called [[Nia (fancy sundress) (xenoblade)|Fancy Sundress]].

Appears in [[Xenoblade Chronicles 3]] as the [b]Queen of Agnus.[/b] [spoilers]She is recruitable as a Hero in the postgame.[/spoiler]

title: cyborg
body:
An organism that is made up of both [b]cyb[/b]ernetic and [b]org[/b]anic components. In anime, this generally refers to humans that have been altered to be partially [[robot]]ic.

It can be difficult to tell a cyborg apart from an [[android]], especially when dealing with [[original]] characters and those whose origins are unknown. In cases like these, one should examine any visible robotic components. If they appear to be added-on or function as [[prosthesis|prosthetics]], that character is likely a cyborg. If you are unable to determine whether the character is a cyborg or purely robotic, it's best to tag them as [[android]] until more information can be found.

title: silver_wolf_(honkai:_star_rail)
body:
A playable character in [[Honkai: Star Rail]].

A member of the Stellaron Hunters and a genius hacker. Silver Wolf has mastered the skill known as "aether editing", which can be used to tamper with the data of reality. Hence, she always views the universe as a massive immersive simulation game and is eager to clear the stages awaiting ahead. Voiced by [[Asumi Kana]] in Japanese.

She is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[grey hair]] with a [[blue hair|blue]] [[gradient]] and tied into a [[drill hair|drill]] [[ponytail]], [[grey eyes]], and [[small breasts]]. Her default outfit consists of a [[black jacket|black]] [[cropped jacket]], white [[crop top]], black [[sports bra]], [[black shorts|black]] [[short shorts]], differently-colored [[thigh strap]]s, [[goggles]] [[eyewear on head|on her head]], [[fishnet socks]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[boots]].

[spoiler]She is revealed to be a member of Manus Vindictae, helping them assassinating important figures of her era, and accelerating World War 1. In the end, she was captured by The Foundation, but she enters deep illusion due to PTSD, thinking she still in Vienna. [/spoiler]

She is voiced by Ella Jonas Farlinger in English and [[Asakura Azumi]] in Japanese.

title: kaiju
body:
[b]Kaiju[/b] (怪獣) is a Japanese word that means "strange beast," but often translated in English as "monster." Specifically, it is used to refer to a genre of tokusatsu entertainment involving giant monsters.

Related terms include kaiju eiga (怪獣映画, monster movie), a film featuring kaiju, kaijin (怪人, humanoid monsters) and daikaiju (大怪獣, giant monster), specifically meaning the larger variety of monsters.

The most famous kaiju is [[Godzilla]]. Other well-known kaiju include [[Mothra]], [[Anguirus]], [[Rodan]], [[Gamera]], and [[King Ghidorah]].

h4. See also

* [[Gamera (series)|]]
* [[Godzilla (series)|]]
* [[Pacific Rim]]
* [[Ultra Series]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Kaiju":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kaiju]

title: loincloth
body:
Any of several ancient styles of garment designed to cover the genitals. Usually made from a folded and tied length of cloth, sometimes held in place by a belt. If it has a dangling length of cloth hanging in front and/or or behind, that part is called, for Danbooru's purposes, a [[pelvic curtain]]. 

[[Fundoshi]] are a range of specifically Japanese styles of loincloth. The loincloth's modern replacements are [[panties]], [[briefs]], and [[boxers]].

Both [[loincloth]] and [[fundoshi]] nowadays are used as festival clothing (usually with [[happi]], or alone) , as a [[swimsuit]] (when worn at the [[beach]]) and occasionally, as [[underwear]] (usually worm under [[kimono]], or [[Japanese armor]] etc). Make sure to use the appropriate tag when tagging them.

If the loincloth is attached to a full-body clothing garment, consider tagging [[tabard]] as well [tn](post #7734925)[/tn].

h4. See also
* [[Fundoshi]]
* [[Naked tabard]]
* [[Pelvic curtain]]
* [[Tabard]]
* [[White male swimwear]] 

h4. External links

title: medic_(isekai_mokushiroku_mynoghra)
body:
One of Mynoghra's normal units produced by Eternal Nation's Clinic facility. They're tall humanoid creatures wrapped entirely in black with a [[plague doctor]] motif. Concealed beneath their robes they have large eyes, shriveled flesh, bent limbs, swollen lumps with darkened skin and ferocious claws, as they're actually Brain Eaters. They're obsessed with humans to the point of wearing the raw flesh they skin off their victims and they refer to humans as "hueman". Contrary to their appearance, they're loud, cheerful and use overly exaggerated gestures.

Normal units don't have unique names, but Takuto named three Medics as Ichiro, Jiro and Saburo.

title: donkey_kong_64
body:
The [[Donkey Kong_(series)|]] franchise's first and only 3D adventure platformer, released in 1999 on the [[Nintendo 64]]. 

The Kongs must race against time to stop [[King K. Rool]] from using his doomsday weapon, the Blast-o-Matic, from destroying DK Isles.

Along with [[Donkey Kong]] and [[Diddy Kong]] a new lineup of playable Kongs are added: [[Lanky Kong]], [[Tiny Kong]] and [[Chunky Kong]].

title: wario_land:_shake_it!
body:
The final entry in the [i][[Wario Land]][/i] series and developed primarily outside of [[Nintendo]] by Good-Feel, released on the [[Wii]].

The Shake Dimension is under peril due to the marauding of the [[Shake King]] and kidnapping of [[Queen Merelda]]. [[Wario]] is uninterested about the plight of the escaped [[Merfle_(wario_land)|]]'s homeworld until it's mentioned that the Shake King also stole the Bottomless Coin Sack, which Wario now wants for himself. Making a deal, Wario has a change of heart and agrees to help the Merfle to acquire this treasure.

Notable for bringing back a redesigned [[Captain Syrup]].
other_names: ワリオランドシェイク

title: shop_owner_(wario_land)
body:
A character in [[Wario Land 4]]. A mysterious entity that runs the Item Shop before each Boss Door. 

The entity will use the items purchased to damage the boss preemptively before the battle begins. Some of the items purchased do not give you a physical item, but instead will have the Shop Owner transform into different creatures to do the damage themselves. These transformations are the [i]Black Dog[/i], the [i]Large Lips[/i], the [i]Big Fist[/i] and the [i]Black Dragon[/i].

h6.All items:
* Apple Bomb
* Blast Cannon
* Vizorman
* Bugle
* [[Black_Dog_(wario_land)|Black Dog]]
* [[Large_Lips_(wario_land)|Large Lips]]
* [[big_fist_(wario_land)|Big Fist]]
* [[black_dragon_(wario_land)|Black Dragon]]

You can also order a free "Smile", but it doesn't do anything. 

[spoiler]Its true identity is that of [[Princess Shokora]].[/spoiler]

title: virtual_boy_wario_land
body:
The second [i][[Wario Land]][/i] entry, released in 1995 on the ill-fated [[Virtual Boy]].

 [[Wario]], vacationing at the Awazon River Basin, notices a group of creatures carrying treasure into a vault full of riches. Wanting the vault he attempts to steal it's contents for himself, but the ground opens from under him. Now lost in the caverns, he explores to take all the treasure he can find.

title: ultima_(fft)
body:
Primary antagonist of [i][[FINAL FANTASY TACTICS]][/i].
Previously localized as [b]Altima[/b], before the [i]War of the Lions[/i] re-releases.

She has two forms.  The first (and most popular), the [b]High Seraph[/b], is of a succubus-like woman in a red [[leotard]] with [[silver hair|silver]]/[[white hair]], [[red eyes]], [[angel wings]] and [[head wings]].

Her final, monstrous form, the [b]Arch Seraph[/b], resembles a gigantic suit of [[skeleton|skeletal]] armor with [[bat wings]].  (e.g. post #304581)

title: wario_land:_super_mario_land_3
body:
Direct sequel to [i][[Super Mario Land 2|Super Mario Land 2: 6 Golden Coins]][/i], the third and final entry in the Super Mario Land series and the beginning of the [i][[Wario land]][/i] series. 

Released in 1994 on the [[Game Boy]], [[Wario]], reeling from his defeat at the hands of [[Mario]] and still wishing for a castle of his own, sets out to steal the riches of the Black Sugar Gang for himself when word spreads of their theft of the Golden [[Princess Peach|Toadstool]] Statue.

title: mandy_(grim_adventures)
body: Mandy is the third titular major protagonist of [[The Grim Adventures of Billy & Mandy]]. She is best friends with Billy and Grim. She is a devious girl from Endsville. In stark contrast to her cheerful, talkative, uniquely funny best friend Billy, she is shown to be grumpy, intelligent, quiet, bitter and utterly ruthless with no redeeming qualities whatsoever.

title: azur_lane:_slow_ahead
body:
An [[Azur Lane]] slice-of-life manga by [[Hori (hori no su)|]], set around the schooling and daily adventures of the starter destroyer shipgirls [[Javelin (Azur Lane)|]], [[Ayanami (Azur Lane)|]], [[Laffey (Azur Lane)|]] and their advisor [[Z23 (Azur Lane)|]].

Adapted into an anime in early 2021 that is not only different in genre and emotional tone to the original [i]Azur Lane[/i] anime, but also made at least partly in-house, as Candybox has studio credit alongside Yostar Pictures. The series also features episode [[end card]]s drawn by fan artists.

Use this tag for the actual 4koma itself or for things referencing either the anime or 4koma (For example, [[North Carolina (Azur Lane)|North Carolina]]’s bunny suit from both, which predates [[North Carolina (The Heart's Desire) (Azur Lane)|The Heart's Desire]], would only count if it's black with the outfit tips down or black with her jacket over it). The tag can also be used for skins that originated in the 4koma before becoming available in the game, such as Javelin's [[Javelin (Slow Ahead!) (Azur Lane)|Slow Ahead!]] or the starters' fantasy/RPG-themed skins.

h4. See also

* pool #13731 (Azur Lane - Official 4Koma "Slow Ahead!")

h4. External links

title: praise_the_sun
body:
[i]"The sun is a wondrous body, like a magnificent father! If only I could be so grossly incandescent..."[/i]

A pose involving stretching out one's arms upwards and tilting one's head towards the sky, as if one was ready to embrace the sun. 

While this pose is most commonly associated with [[Dark Souls I|Dark Souls's]] [[Solaire of Astora]] and the Warriors of Sunlight, it first appeared in [[Demon's Souls]] as an alternate animation for casting miracles while equipping the Ring of Sincere Prayer.

The emoticon associated with it is [b]\o/[/b]. The Solaire specific version is [b]\[T]/[/b].

title: yukimura_ryuuko_(ryuuko)
body: Original character belonging to "Ryuuko/BasedJunyou":[https://twitter.com/BasedJunyou], usually seen in commissioned artwork by various artists. She is depicted as Ryuuko's [[female commander (azur lane)|commander]] character, hailing from the Maple Monarchy ([[Azur Lane]]'s representation of [[Canada]], mentioned in [[Fortune (Azur Lane)|Fortune]]'s quotes). The character creator also came up with the following biography for the character in a Reddit post of the first art featuring her (Post #5608350), since deleted: [expand=Biography] * Name: Ryūko Yukimura (雪村 龍子 – Yukimura Ryūko) * Date of birth: February 14, 1996 * Place of birth: Seneca, Ontario, Maple Monarchy * Nationality: Bangladeshi-Canadian * Naval college graduation date: May 1, 2018 * Age: 27, as of February 2023 * Height: 5'3" (160 cm) * Weight: 115 lbs (52 kg) * Rank: Admiral (January 2023-present) * Appearance: As depicted in the drawing! * Three sizes: 84-56-83 * Default attire: As depicted in the drawing! * Hobbies: Sports, video games, astronomy, digital art, model ships, naval history, MMA, fashion (of all kinds) * Family: HMS Prince of Wales (wife), Caroline Beau (adoptive mother), Ichiro Yukimura (paternal grandfather, deceased), unnamed deceased biological parents * CV: [[Mizuki Nana|Nana Mizuki]] * Description A renowned flag officer known as the Dragon of Azur Lane, Ryūko Yukimura is the overall fleet commander of Port Pacific – a naval base at the island of O'ahu, Hawaii. At the tender age of twenty-three, “Yuko” was promoted from Lieutenant (OF-2) to Commodore (OF-6) as the solution the Wisdom Cube Affinity Project – a confidential research endeavour which aimed to seek exceptionally competent Kansen commanders, by virtue of their inherent ‘match’ with shipgirls. In September 2019, an attack on Port Pacific (modern day Pearl Harbour) by the Sakura Empire mobilized Azur Lane. Thereafter, a bitter eighteen-month conflict with the powerful island nation began. Yuko’s prodigous handling of the ensuing conflict, deployment of strategy, and peerless care for his Kansen subordinates catapulted her through the flag officer ranks as Port Pacific stymied the Sakura Empire’s ambitions. Due to her unprecedented ascent through the ranks – and by virtue of her given name – she was awarded her nickname by the Empire admiralty. In 2014 – when she was eighteen – Yuko’s hometown was obliterated by a Siren attack. The invaders, who had used the St. Lawrence River as a buffer, opened a portal at Lake Ontario. The only reason she survived is because she decided to go to work earlier than normal that day (she worked at a retail store which had an underground bunker in case of emergency – thanks to the CEO’s paranoia about Sirens and other disasters). Riddled with Survivor’s Guilt and PTSD, she had thrown herself into her studies/training while enrolled at the Peterborough Naval Academy. Despite counseling, psychiatry, and medication he was unable to make friends with his peers at the academy – who froze her out due to a lack of understanding of her conditions (that Yuko, in turn, never properly explained to begin with as it was too sensitive a topic). By her senior year at the academy, however, she had become the undisputed number one cadet in many years – her hard work having paid off. Her only emotional support was her instructor, then-Commodore Caroline Beau – who often conversed with her outside of training hours. Yuko takes a sympathetic, informal stance to her work and understands the immense responsibility that her position entails. In spite of this, her words are nevertheless firm, demanding, and resolute – delivering the comprehension that she wants the absolute best for those around her. Outside of work hours, she is playful and teasing – occasionally making references to pop culture and internet memes. In spite of this, she is also shown to be quite deceptive; as demonstrated in Kitsune’s Oath, withholding Subject Blossom from Akagi but eventually introducing her in the cleanest manner possible – earning her the everlasting respect of the Sakura girls at base. With the help of his beloved port, Yuko eventually overcomes the horrors of her past – and challenges the future with a renewed focus. Here’s the list of her service medals (depicted as undress ribbons), in order of precedence: 1) [[Victoria Cross]] (VC) – Awarded following the defeat of IJN Taihou, IJN Shoukaku, and IJN Zuikaku (among other forces) following the Second Battle of Midway (April 2021). This is the highest honour a Maple Monarchy citizen can receive. 2) Cross of Valour (CV) – Awarded following the defeat of IJN Jintsuu and her forces near the waters of American Samoa (December 2020). This is the second-highest honour a Maple Monarchy citizen can receive. 3) Officer of the Order of Canada (OC) – Awarded by virtue of recognition for her outstanding contribution to the Maple Monarchy, by way of advancing her nation’s interests. Awarded in August 2020. 4) Commander of the Order of Military Merit (CMM) – Recognized for her outstanding contribution to the Maple Monarchy by way of consistently advancing her nation’s military interests. Awarded on August 2020. 5) Member of the Order of Ontario (OOnt) – Awarded to longtime residents of Ontario, who have demonstrated a high level of individual excellence and achievement in any field. In Yuko’s case it is her service to Azur Lane. Awarded in May 2020. 6) Star of Military Valour (SMV) – Awarded following the Battle of the Solomon Islands (May 2020); intended to honour those who have shown conspicuous acts of valour in the face of enemy hostility. 7) Star of Courage (SC) – Awarded following the First Battle of Midway (September 2019). 8) Meritorious Service Cross (military division, MSC) – Awarded in recognition by carrying out meritorious acts bringing benefit and honour for Azur Lane and the Maple Monarchy. Awarded in February 2020. 9) General Campaign Star (GCS) – Awarded following numerous Siren incursions near Hawaii in late 2019. Some other details (meta or otherwise) about Yuko: 1) Her nickname is a reference to Kazuma Kiryu. 2) She shares her favourite hobbies with me. 3) She is actually the gender-bent version of my main SKK OC, Tatsuya Yukimura (“Yuki”). Who, in turn, is completely based on me – if I had grown up in AL's world (well, my version of it). You can read their tale here. 4) Her grandfather immigrated to the Maple Monarchy in the 1960s with his wife. He was a Sakura Empire otaku, so he changed family name (and his) to Yukimura. 5) In a very special universe, she’s the brother-in-law of ArchiveSlave’s SKK OC – Alexander Cochrane. [/expand]

title: snake_eyes_(character)
body:
A character from the [[G.I. Joe]] toy line, comic books, cartoon and live action film series. 

[b]Snake Eyes[/b] (also released as [b]Snake-Eyes[/b]) is one of the original and most known members of the G.I. Joe Team. 

A lone silent commando clad in a black outfit and mask, Snake Eyes is an expert in unorthodox [[martial arts]] and advanced [[close-quarters combat]], hand-to-hand combat, infiltration, stealth and firearms. He is one of the most prominent characters in the G.I. Joe franchise, having appeared in every series of the franchise since its inception. 

He never speaks and only communicates through hand gestures. To this day, nobody knows if he can actually say a word. 

Snake-Eyes debuted as an [[action figure]] in 1982. His figure is considered the most popular G.I. Joe toy ever, with 68 different versions released as of 2014.

He is portrayed by actor/stuntman "Ray Park":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ray_Park in the 2009 live-action film [i]"G.I. Joe: The Rise of Cobra":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G.I._Joe:_The_Rise_of_Cobra [/i] and the 2013 sequel [i]"G.I. Joe: Retaliation":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G.I._Joe:_Retaliation].[/i]

title: gouf
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series. It first appeared in [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] from 1979.

[b]MS-07B Gouf[/b]

A blue, mono-eyed [[Zeon]] [[mobile suit]] specifically designed for [[close-quarters combat]]. It has a distinct horn on its head, spiked shoulders, and a tentacle whip which emerges from its right arm. Notably piloted by [[Ramba Ral]].

A variation known as the [[Gouf Custom]] is piloted by [[Norris Packard]] from [[Gundam 08th MS Team]]. The Gouf was redesigned for [[Gundam SEED Destiny]], and is known as the [[GOUF Ignited]]. It is most notably piloted by [[Heine Westenfluss]] and [[Yzak Joule]].

Despite what the casual mecha anime [[otaku]] may think, the Gouf [i]"is not a [[Zaku]] boy, not a Zaku...".[/i] (ザクとは違うのだよ、ザクとは!)

title: chris_redfield
body:
[b]Chris Redfield[/b] is a Special Operations Agent (SOA) of the Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance (BSAA), of which he is a founding member. Formerly, he served in the US Air Force; before moving on to law enforcement as a member of the RPD's Special Tactics And Rescue Service's (S.T.A.R.S.) Alpha Team. After S.T.A.R.S. were disbanded following the Raccoon City Incident, he and his partner, [[Jill Valentine]], became members of a Private Regional Biohazard Containment Unit (BCU), and took part in the fall of Umbrella in 2003. 

Chris is the older brother of [[Claire Redfield]] and one of few survivors of the mansion incident, during the Arklay Mountains outbreak in 1998. In addition to his qualification to pilot fixed-wing aircraft, Chris has been trained strictly in several fighting techniques like [[close-quarters combat]], is an expert in knife and firearm combat, and is also gifted with great accuracy.

Also notorious for punching a boulder in the climax of [[Resident Evil 5]].

h4.Appearance
Chris is a [[muscular male|muscular man]] with [[black hair]] and [[blue eyes]]. His appearance varies throughout the series.

* [[Resident Evil 1]]: Chris wears a [[police uniform]] with [[white shirt]], [[black pants]], [[bulletproof vest]], [[fingerless gloves]], and black boots.
* [[Resident Evil 5]]: Chris has a [[green shirt]], [[gloves]], [[grey pants]] and a [[green footwear|green shoes]]. His appearance changes noticeably, looking much more muscular compared to Resident Evil 1 .
* [[Resident Evil 6]]: Chris wears a similar outfit to the ones he wore in Resident Evil 5, albeit he sports a [[grey pants]], [[green shirt]], [[bulletproof vest]] and [[gloves]].
* [[Resident Evil 7: Biohazard]]: In Resident Evil 7: biohazard, Chris design changed to a less muscular body and a [[brown hair]], he sports a [[black jacket]], [[gloves]], [[black pants]], [[bulletproof vest]], [[black shoes]] and [[knee pads]]. 
* [[Resident Evil Village]]: Chris has a much more matured appearance in Resident Evil Village, he sports a [[black coat]] along with [[black shirt]], [[black pants]], [[gloves]] and black shoes.

h4. See also

* [[Chrisposting (meme)]]

body:
A dish consisting of [[spaghetti]], pasta sauce, and [[meatball|meatballs]] mixed together. Contrary to popular belief in cartoons and other media, Spaghetti and Meatballs is not a traditional Italian dish but a Italian-American dish as its creation was the result of early Italian immigrants combining two different dishes from Italy (Spaghetti with pasta sauce and small meatballs) and using ingredients available in their new home in the United States like extra beef which is plentiful in America.

title: chidejika
body:
Chidejika is a [[mascot]] created as a spokesperson for the [[Japan Commercial Broadcasters Association]] as a preparation for Japanese TV stations to switch to digital programming by July 24, 2011. Chidejika is an upright-walking deer wearing a yellow leotard.

The name actually means "terrestrial digitalization." The chi (地) means earth. Deji (デジ) is short for digital. Jika (ジカ) means deer. 

The mascot was created after the association dropped its original spokesperson, SMAP's Kusanagi Tsuyoshi, following his arrest for indecent exposure. Kusanagi was later reinstated, thus sharing the spokesperson position with Chidejika.

title: armored_personnel_carrier
body:
A [[ground vehicle]] designed to transport [[soldier]]s and equipment into a combat zone.

APCs are fundamentally different from [[tank]]s. Generally speaking, APCs have lighter armor (still strong enough to resist bullets and shrapnel) compared to tanks. They have lighter armament because of their focused transport purpose and for the sake of mobility. Most commonly, APCs are armed with [[machine gun]]s or automatic [[grenade launcher]]s. It can either have wheels or [[caterpillar tracks]], while tanks are always tracked. Some can be amphibious.

Not only the [[military]], [[police]] tactical units also operate it. Sometimes APCs can be utilized as [[ambulance]], especially in battlefield (see post #1085064).

h4. List of APCs

* [[aavp-7a1|AAVP-7]]
* [[BTR-4 Bucephalus]]

body:
[[Mario_(series)|]] character first appearing in [i][[Yume Koujou: Doki Doki Panic]][/i], then later incorporated into the Mario franchise proper with the international version of [i][[Super Mario Bros. 2]][/i]. Birdos were a reoccurring mid-boss and subordinate of [[Wart_(mario)|]] during the attempted conquest of Subcon. Since then however the species has become overall less antagonistic and much more friendlier. 

They are [[reptile_girl|dinosaur-like]] with large snouts in place of a mouth, from which they shoot white [[egg]]s out of to attack. They have long [[eyelashes]], [[eyeshadow]] and wear an [[ornate ring]]. They wear an [[huge_bow|oversized bow]] on the back of their heads as well as have [[claws]].

Birdos come in a variety of colors, though the main color is pink. Compared to [[Toad_(mario)|]]s and [[Yoshi]]s, Birdos are much more consistently represented by a singular individual in a given game, where it's much rarer to see the rest of the species or a multitude in one place.

h4. Official Art
* !post #7938195

Very effective as a stabbing meele weapon for [[close-quarters combat|close quarters combat]] because of its sharpness and low weight which make it very lethal and yet very easy to handle unlike long swords.

title: michael_knight
body:
[spoiler][quote][i]A man... who does not exist....[/i][/quote][/spoiler]

[b]Michael Knight[/b] is a the fictional protagonist character from the American adventure and [[science fiction]] TV series [[Knight Rider]] released in the 80s. 

Played by "David Hasselhoff":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Hasselhoff , Michael is a high-tech modern crime fighter assisted by [[K.I.T.T]]., an advanced artificially intelligent, self-aware and nearly indestructible [[robot]] sports [[car]]. 

He is the primary field agent in the pilot program of his public justice organization, the Foundation for Law and Government (FLAG). 

Michael Knight is a special type of hero, a "modern [[knight]]" who avoids violence whenever possible and generally refrains from using melee weapons or firearms although he is actually a [[Vietnam War]] veteran proficient in [[martial arts]], [[close-quarters combat]] combat and the use of .38 [[revolver]]s and the [[MAC-10/11|MAC-10]] [[submachine gun]].

Michael [spoiler]was actually born Michael Arthur Long and was a LAPD detective working undercover, when he was shot in the face during a case and left for dead. Given a new face via facial reconstructive surgery by the FLAG organization, Long was resurrected as Michael Knight and deployed as their agent (as seen in the series pilot episodes).[/spoiler] 

h4. See also

* "Wikipedia article":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Knight_(Knight_Rider)_

title: kusanagi_motoko
body:
[b]Major Kusanagi Motoko[/b] is the main character of the [[Ghost In The Shell]] [[cyberpunk]] series.

Major Kusanagi is the serious and very competent squad leader of [[police|Public Security Section 9's counter-terrorist and anti-crime unit]].

The Major is a full body [[cyborg]] with short hair with long sidelocks. Her hair color changes from series to series; from blue in the original manga (and [i]Arise[/i]), black in the movies, to purple in [i]S.A.C.[/i] Her eye color also changes, being blue (movies), green or red depending on the show. She is often seen wearing a pink [[leotard]] with pink [[thighhighs]], black [[bodysuit|battle armor]], or a yellow [[police uniform|police officer's uniform]].

The Major is also an expert in systems hacking, infiltration, [[close-quarters combat]], [[martial arts]], and is extremely proficient with many types of ballistic weapons.

title: eve_online
body:
A science-fiction MMORPG developed by Icelandic company CCP Games. It is currently the only single-shard MMORPG in existence, meaning all players share a single world (called New Eden) of over 14,000 star systems, running on the gaming industry's most powerful server.

Players take control of a 'capsuleer', an augmented human (there are no alien species in the universe, with the possible exception of the reclusive Jove, who were originally humans as well, but have undergone extensive genetic modification, resulting in what is practically a new species) whose consciousness is transferred to a clone in the event of death, making the capsuleer immortal. Capsuleers travel in small capsules (hence the name) that protect them from various dangers in space, and which, in turn, are docked into larger ships, creating a conduit between the capsuleer brain and the ship systems in order to pilot the ship.

Expansions used to be issued twice a year, but towards the end of 2014, CCP Games switched to a release cycle of 4-6 weeks between expansions.

The game is (in)famous for its steep learning curve, stemming from the many opportunities and possibilities players are faced with, all of which are available from day one.

h4. External links
* "Website":http://www.eveonline.com

title: foreman_spike
body:
A character from [i][[Wrecking Crew]][/i]. Described as a "mean old man" (意地悪おじさん) in the original Japanese manual and as a "Foreman" in the original English manual. He attempts to impede the progress of [[Mario]] or [[Luigi]] by destroying any walls, ladders, or pillars they are near, forcing them to fall. Functionally he performs the same role as Luigi's CPU did in [i]Vs. Wrecking Crew[/i].

While most of his appearances have very different looks from each other, his most consistent traits are that he wears [[sunglasses]] and has a [[beard]], though in [i]Wrecking Crew '98[/i] he is clean shaven with a visible [[cleft chin]]. In [i]Mobile Golf[/i] he was given a more [[fat_man|rotund]] body similar to that of [[Wario]]. 

Was originally known as [b]Blackey/Blacky[/b] (ブラッキー), until his appearance in [[the Super Mario Bros. Movie]] led to him adopting his international name [b]Spike[/b] (スパイク) in Japan.

h4. External link

* "Mario Wiki":[https://www.mariowiki.com/Foreman_Spike]

title: olga_of_kyiv
body:
[b]Olga of Kyiv[/b] was the ruler of the [[Ukraine|Kyivan Rus']] from 945 to 960 (regent for her son Sviatoslav) and was later named a saint by the Eastern Orthodox Church for her efforts to convert the Kyivan Rus' to Christianity.

Another deed she is famous for is her revenge on the Drevlians, who had her husband, Igor of Kyiv, killed.

title: nakayama_racecourse
body:
Horse racecourse in Funabashi, Chiba. As one of the two JRA racecourses (the other beig [[tokyo racecourse|Tokyo]]) in the Tokyo area, it is home to a number of graded races, most notably the Satsuki Sho and Arima Kinen.

* [[Satsuki Sho]] (mid-April)
* [[Sprinters Stakes]] (late-September)
* [[Nakayama Daishogai]] (late-December)
* [[Arima Kinen]] (late-December)
* [[Hopeful Stakes]] (late-December)

[[Type 4 (girls' frontline)|]]'s fifth skin from [[Girls' Frontline]], as part of the 'The Night the Bonfire Blazes' skin collection from 2023.

She wears a [[white robe]] over a [[black dress]], a [[white hat|white]] [[witch hat]], [[white thighhighs]], [[black footwear|black]] [[fold-over boots|fold-over]] [[high heels]], and [[jack-o'-lantern hair ornament]]s. She may be [[broom riding|riding a broom]] with her weapon suspended by [[belt]]s under it, with a [[jack-o'-lantern]] suspended from the gun.

title: droopy_dog_(cartoon)
body:
This is a series of animated shorts from 1943 to 1958 featuring the titular [[Droopy]] character by cartoonist Tex Avery. The character would later appear in [[Who Framed Roger Rabbit]], [[Tom and Jerry]], and other shows. On Japanese TV, the Droopy shorts were aired sandwiched between Tom and Jerry shorts, so he's often imagined in association with them.

h4. See also

* [[Sheep Wrecked]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia - Droopy":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Droopy]

title: droopy
body:
[[toon (style)|Cartoon]] character created by Tex Avery, an animator who worked for [[metro-goldwyn-mayer|MGM]], first appearing in 1943.

Droopy is an [[personification|anthropomorphic]] white [[basset hound]] with droopy jowls, [[half-closed eyes]], and [[floppy ears]]. He was the protagonist in his own set of [[Droopy Dog (cartoon)|]] shorts from 1943 to 1958 by cartoonist Tex Avery, and would later make appearances in [[Who Framed Roger Rabbit]], [[Tom and Jerry]], and other shows.

On Japanese TV, the Droopy shorts were aired sandwiched between [[Tom and Jerry]] shorts, so he's often imagined in association with them.

h4. See also

* [[Cartoon Network]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia - Droopy":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Droopy]

title: bitey_(arknights)
body:
One of [[Dusk (arknights)|]]'s Ink Spirits.

[i]A common Ink Spirit, named by the painter herself. It's very smart and actually understands human speech. Apparently some kind of communal organism, it gets lonely when left by itself. It has done many a mean thing out of amusement, for it's just an Ink Spirit, no matter how smart.[/i]

title: captain_falcon
body:
A [[F-Zero]] racer, the pilot of the [[Blue Falcon]] and renowned bounty hunter. Outside of hailing from Port Town, much of his past is shrouded in mystery.

His popularity has skyrocketed since appearing in the original [[Super Smash Bros.]] game for [[Nintendo 64]], giving him many memorable voice quips like [i]"Show me your moves!"[/i] and making him best known for his devastating attack: the [[falcon_punch|Falcon Punch]]!
