title: foreign_disciples_(fate/grand_order)
body:
Major antagonists in the second arc of [[Fate/Grand Order]], seven servants summoned by the Alien God, [[U-Olga Marie]], to assist the [[Crypters (fate/grand order)|]] in replacing greater human history with that of the Lostbelts. [spoiler]It turns out that unbeknownst to her, U-Olga Marie is also one of the disciples rather than the mastermind.[/spoiler] This tag applies if [b]at least 3[/b] are present in an image.

The disciples include:
* The God, [[U-Olga Marie]]. [spoiler]Manifested by mistake but repurposed to serve as the overseer for the other disciples. Initially believed to the Alien God itself.[/spoiler]
* The Priest, [[Rasputin (fate)|]]. [spoiler]Summoned to surveil the Crypters.[/spoiler]
* The Malignant Incarnation, [[Ashiya Douman (fate)|]]. [spoiler]Summoned to surveil the Lostbelt Kings and make sure none of the Lostbelts would overtake the [[Olympus (fate/grand order)|Greek Lostbelt]].[/spoiler]
* The Atlas Slayer, [spoiler][[Senji Muramasa (fate)|]]. Summoned to prevent [[Kirschtaria Wodime]]'s plot to destroy the Alien God.[/spoiler]
* The Detective, [spoiler][[Sherlock Holmes (fate)|]]. Summoned to help Chaldea defeat [[Goetia (fate)|]] and the first 6 Lostbelts. Had his memories wiped and defected to Chaldea.[/spoiler]
* The Professor, [spoiler][[James Moriarty (Ruler) (fate)|]]. Summoned to kill the traitor [[Sherlock Holmes (fate)|]] and then take control of Chaldea.[/spoiler]
* The Count, [spoiler][[Alessandro di Cagliostro (fate)|]]. Summoned to observe Chaldea.[/spoiler]
[[Koyanskaya (fate)|]] was initially believed by Novum Chaldea to be one of the disciples before being revealed to be an independent party working alongside them. For tagging purposes she may be included in the count.

h4. See Also
* [[Crypters (fate/grand order)|]]

title: crypters_(fate/grand_order)
body:
Major antagonists in the second arc of [[Fate/Grand Order]], looking to supplant proper human history with their Lostbelts. Previously members of Chaldea's A-Team, who were killed during the inciting incident of the first arc and subsequently revived by the Alien God. This tag applies if [b]at least three[/b] are present in an image.

The seven Crypters are:
* [[Kadoc Zemlupus]], supervising the [[Anastasia (lostbelt) (fate/grand order)|Russian Lostbelt]] with his servant [[Anastasia (fate)|]]
* [[Ophelia Phamrsolone]], supervising the [[Gotterdammerung (fate/grand order)|Scandinavian Lostbelt]] with her servant [spoiler][[Surtr (fate)|]][/spoiler]
* [[Akuta Hinako]], supervising the [[S I N (fate/grand order)|Chinese Lostbelt]] with her servant [spoiler][[Prince of Lan Ling (fate)|]][/spoiler]
* [[Scandinavia Peperoncino]], supervising the [[Yugakshetra (fate/grand order)|Indian Lostbelt]] with his servant [spoiler][[Ashwatthama (fate)|]][/spoiler]
* [[Kirschtaria Wodime]], supervising the [[Atlantis (fate/grand order)|Greek Lostbelt]] with his servants [[Caenis (fate)|]], [spoiler][[Castor (fate)|]], and [[Pollux (fate)|]][/spoiler]
* [[Beryl Gut]], supervising the [[Avalon le Fae (fate/grand order)|British Lostbelt]] with his servant [spoiler][[Morgan le Fay (fate)|]][/spoiler]
* [[Daybit Sem Void]], supervising the [[Nahui Mictlan (fate/grand order)|South American Lostbelt]] with his servant [spoiler][[Tezcatlipoca (fate)|]][/spoiler]

h4. See Also
* [[Foreign Disciples (fate/grand order)|]]

title: black_shadow
body:
[[F-Zero]] racer and the pilot of the [[Black Bull]]. The feared evil Space Emperor and the arch-nemesis of [[Captain Falcon]].

Tired of his henchmen continually being captured and his plans thwarted by the bounty hunter, he enters the F-Zero races with the sole purpose of killing Captain Falcon in front of billions of spectators across the galaxy.

title: cannon_illefuto
body:
A fictional manned giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It appears in [[Turn A Gundam]].

[b]SPA-51 Cannon Illefuto[/b]

An excavated artillery [[mobile suit]] dating back to the Dark History, it has high firepower due to the backpack-mounted five-barrel gatling gun. Others armaments include a vulcan gun on the left side of its head and an arm-mounted shield with integrated beam saber emitter for close-quarters combat.
other_names: キャノン・イルフート

title: monique_l'amoreaux
body:
The wife of Super Arrow and pilot of the [[Queen Meteor]]. 

Due to her husbands lack of driving experience, she enters the [[F-Zero]] races to help him. A former [[race queen]] for the F-Zero circuit before getting married.

title: gm_kai
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series.

[b]RGM-79C GM Kai[/b]

Also referred to as the [[gm_(mobile_suit)|GM]] Type C, the upgraded type was more powerful than its predecessor but still somewhat average in performance. It was a versatile, serviceable [[mobile suit]] that satisfactorily filled the needs of the [[Earth Federation]] during peacetime.

body:

A clone of [[Captain Falcon]], created with stolen DNA during Captain Falcon's hospitalization after the Huge Accident 3 years ago prior to F-Zero X. His equal in every way.

title: pico_(f-zero)
body:
[[F-Zero]] racer and the pilot of the [[Wild Goose]]. An [[alien]] that hails from Death Wind, he has an extremely aggressive and cold personality. A former soldier and rumored hitman.

The Huge Accident 3 years ago prior to F-Zero X is said to be due to his reckless and dangerous driving.

title: moana_(movie)
body:
Moana is a 2016 American animated musical fantasy adventure film produced by Walt Disney Animation Studios and released by Walt Disney Pictures. The film was directed by John Musker and Ron Clements, co-directed by Chris Williams and Don Hall, and produced by Osnat Shurer, from a screenplay written by Jared Bush, and based on a story conceived by Clements, Musker, Williams, Hall, Pamela Ribon, and the writing team of Aaron Kandell and Jordan Kandell.
The film stars [[the rock (dwayne johnson)|Dwayne Johnson]] and Auliʻi Cravalho in her film debut as the voice of [[moana waialiki|the eponymous character]] and also features the voices of Rachel House, Temuera Morrison, Jemaine Clement, Nicole Scherzinger, and Alan Tudyk. It features original songs written by Lin-Manuel Miranda, Opetaia Foa'i, and Mark Mancina, and an original musical orchestral score also composed by Mancina. The film is set in ancient Polynesia and tells the story of Moana, the strong-willed daughter of a chief of a coastal village, who is chosen by the ocean itself to reunite a mystical relic with the goddess Te Fiti. When a blight strikes her island, Moana sets sail in search of Maui, a legendary demigod, in hopes of returning the relic to Te Fiti and saving her people. The screenplay takes inspiration from Polynesian myths.

title: zorro
body:
A fictional character created in 1919 by American pulp writer Johnston McCulley, appearing in works set in the Pueblo of Los Angeles in Alta California. He is typically portrayed as a dashing masked vigilante who defends the commoners and Indigenous peoples of California against corrupt, tyrannical officials and other villains. His signature all-black costume includes a [[black cape]], a hat known as a sombrero cordobés, and an [[eye mask]] covering the upper half of his face. 

Often considered the original American superhero, his antics would inspire both Superman and Batman.

title: moana_waialiki
body: Moana of Motunui is the title character of the 2016 Walt Disney Animation Studios film [[Moana (movie)|]]. Created by directors Ron Clements and John Musker, Moana is voiced by Hawaiian actress and singer Auliʻi Cravalho. As a toddler, she is voiced by Louise Bush. Moana returns in the sequel film Moana 2, which premiered in November of 2024, again voiced by Cravalho, as well as a live-action remake film, in 2026, in which she will be portrayed by Catherine Laga'aia.

title: maui_(moana)
body: Maui is a demigod of South Pacific legends. Despite his status, Maui finds himself torn between the worlds of humanity and deity, feeling "stuck in the middle". Nevertheless, he finds enjoyment in showcasing his godlike abilities to others.

title: neon_genesis_evangelion
body:
One of the most popular anime of all time on top of being a popular [[mecha]] series, created by [[Anno Hideaki]] initially with [[GAINAX]] and now with his company [[Studio Khara]]. It was first released as a TV anime series in October 1995.

Originally planned as a parody of the traditional [[super robot]] mecha anime genre tropes at the time (according to creator Anno), it surprisingly became an extremely successful and long lasting franchise despite its mentally and socially troubled protagonists [spoilers]and Anno's original intention to troll super robot mecha [[otaku]][/spoilers].

The [b]Evangelion[/b] franchise also spans the initial manga, and many spin-offs in various media.

title: kogal
body:
[b]Kogal[/b] (コギャル), a substyle of [[Gyaru]] (ギャル), is a [[fashion]] trend among young female Japanese high school students.

They follow the trends of gyaru fashion in their heavy makeup (especially around the eyes), sometimes [[tan]] skin, use of English-influenced slang (kogyarugo or コギャル語), coloured (and often bleached) hair, and trendy gyaru style fashion. Since they are school girls, they use their [[school uniform]] as their fashion statement, often wearing their uniform skirts very short and paired with [[loose socks]].

If there aren't any obvious signs of kogal (school uniform, [[loose socks]], [[scrunchie]], etc) then it's recommended to just tag the image with the more general [[gyaru]].

h4. See also

title: black_adam
body: Black Adam, real name Teth-Adam , is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by [[DC Comics]]. He was created by Otto Binder and C. C. Beck, and first appeared in the debut issue of Fawcett Comics' The Marvel Family comic book in December 1945. Since DC Comics licensed and acquired Fawcett's characters in the 1970s, Black Adam has endured as one of the most popular archenemies of the superhero [[shazam|Captain Marvel / Shazam]] and the Marvel Family alongside Doctor Sivana and Mister Mind.

title: dayflower
body:
[b][i]Commelina[/i][/b], commonly called dayflower, is a genus of [[flower]]ing plants in the family [i]Commelinaceae[/i]. Commonly represented by [i]Commelina communis[/i] (Asiatic dayflower), native to East and Southeast Asia.

Commelinas are small flowers that are usually blue, but they also come in shades of white, yellow, purple, and pink. The flowers emerge from a boat-like sheath called a spathe that surrounds the flower stem.  Common species, such as the Asiatic dayflower, have a distinctive appearance: The flowers appear to have only two petals at the top, but there is actually a third, inconspicuous white petal at the bottom. They also have a distinctive pistil and stamens that curve upward.

h4. Examples
* !asset #24009824: Flower
* !asset #24010375: Flower and its spathe

title: tutankhamun_(fate)
body:
Archer-class Servant introduced in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. One of the most famous Pharaohs of Ancient Egypt, Tutankhamun acceded to the throne at 9 years of age. During his reign he undid the shift of Ancient Egyptian religion caused by Akhenaten, who is believed to have been Tutankhamun's father. Tutankhamun's reign ended when died around age 18.

Tutankhamun was made famous in modern times by the discovery of his tomb in 1922. Compared to a lot of other pharaohs, Tutankhamun's tomb was largely undisturbed, and a lot of its contents, including treasures and his undisturbed mummy, were left intact. This discovery led to a renewed interest in Ancient Egypt by the public. The deaths of various individuals who were involved in the excavation of his tomb led to popular rumors regarding the "curse of the pharaoh".

title: tatara_kogasa
body:
The "Cheery Forgotten Umbrella". 

Stage 2 mid-boss and boss, as well as Extra Stage mid-boss of [[Touhou]]'s [i][[Undefined Fantastic Object]][/i], and Stage 3 mid-boss of [i][[Ten Desires]][/i]. A [i]karakasa[/i] youkai who frequently tries (in vain) to surprise humans. She carries her [[purple umbrella|purple]] [[karakasa obake]] with a [[tongue]] almost always sticking out, although there is some debate as to whether the girl or the umbrella (or both) is the real Kogasa. Fanworks often depict her under the mercy of [[Kochiya Sanae]] due to the latter's scathing words against her back in UFO.

Due to similarities in her style of dress to [[Kazami Yuuka]] (designated by [[ZUN (artist)|]] as "youkai moe"), along with her being perceived as a highly moe character in her own right, Kogasa is often referred to by fans as "the new youkai moe."

h4. Appearance

* !asset #24008618
* !asset #24008619

She has [[short hair|short]] [[blue hair]] and [[heterochromia]] with [[blue eyes|blue]] and [[red eyes]]. She wears a [[white shirt]] with [[juliet sleeves]], a [[blue vest]], a [[blue skirt]], and [[geta]]. In [[Wild and Horned Hermit]] she wears a [[frilled capelet|frilled]] [[blue capelet]] instead of her vest. 

h4. See also

* Pool #2555 - Surprise!  For instances where she actually manages to surprise someone.

title: patterned_hair
body:
Hair with a pattern that would be impossible to replicate on real hair. Usually [[multicolored hair]].

Think of, for example, painting some stars on your hair. Whenever it moves, the star would break up into smaller hair strands.
As such, gradient hair and streaked hair can be replicated, but print hair cannot.

h4. See Also

title: wicker_man
body:
An ancient celtic druidic means of sacrifice, a large effigy in the shape of a man is built out of straw, where the condemned or simply slaves are put within and set ablaze.
The only known source of the wicker man's existence is from the writings of Gaius Julius Caesar and earlier writings by Posidonius the historian.

For the Noble Phantasm wielded by [[Cu Chulainn (Caster) (fate)|]] in [[Fate/Grand Order]], use [[Wicker Man (fate)]].

title: tennis_no_ouji-sama
body:
A [[tennis]]-themed sports (and action) manga and anime series written and illustrated by [[Konomi Takeshi]]. It was serialized in [[Weekly Shounen Jump]] from 1999 to 2008. Localized as [b]The Prince of Tennis[/b] outside Japan.

The series is famous for an absurd amount of violence that is best compared to martial arts manga, with superhuman abilities, special moves, and life-threatening injuries. This unusual approach of sports manga is intentional on behalf of Konomi, who wanted it to be a departure from other popular sports manga and anime series at that time.

title: witness_holes
body:
"The term 'witness holes' generally refers to the small openings on the back or side-face of a handgun magazine allowing operators to visually confirm how many cartridges are loaded. Most modern semi-automatic handguns come standard with magazines featuring witness holes. It may also refer to the hole drilled in the top of a pistol barrel chamber so a user may visually confirm if there is a round chambered. This serves as a type of loaded-chamber indicator (LCI) but has no mechanical parts and does not allow for confirmation in low-light conditions when compared to a traditional LCI."

—SIG Sauer Glossary https://www.sigsauer.com/glossary/witness-holes/

title: sampo_koski
body:
A playable character in [[Honkai: Star Rail]]. Voiced by [[Hirakawa Daisuke]]. 

He is portrayed with [[medium hair|medium-length]] [[blue hair]] with [[white hair|white]] [[streaked hair|streaked ends]], and a [[muscular]] build. His default outfit consists of a [[black shirt]], [[red jacket|red]] [[cropped jacket]], [[black gloves]], single [[shoulder armor]] on his right side, [[black pants]], and [[brown footwear|brown shoes]]. 

He is an eloquent mercenary from The Underworld who does all sorts of jobs for his "customer," as long as they don't get paid off with a higher price.

He makes a suprise appreance in [[Honkai Impact 3rd]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #7689999: Splash art
* !post #7732642: Eyes of the Prey (signature Light Cone)

h4. Profile
[expand]
A silver-tongued salesman, where there is profit to be made, you can be sure Sampo is nearby.

Sampo's unique knowledge makes it hard not to approach him for help, but becoming his "customer" is not necessarily a good thing.

After all, "customers" can quickly turn into "commodities" for the right price.
[/expand]

title: meta_knight
body:
Meta Knight is a popular character in the [[Kirby_(series)|Kirby series]] and is the second of [[Kirby]]'s rivals, the first being [[King Dedede]]. He follows a code of honor, often providing Kirby with a sword to battle with (only breaking that code when he's not in control of himself, or when the situation is dire), and fights using a golden spiked sword called [[Galaxia (sword)|]]. Meta Knight is also shown to help Kirby sometimes.
 
In the [[kirby:_right_back_at_ya|anime]], he's definitely on Kirby's side, helping him fight against the evil Demon Beasts created by the Holy [[Nightmare (kirby)|]] Company that Dedede buys from them. He shows some relationships with one of Kirby's friends, [[Fumu (kirby)|]], seeing her as a rare source of intelligence. He's also a Star Warrior, having been one before Kirby and having been one of the few survivors of the war between the Galaxy Soldier Army and the Holy Nightmare Company. 

He is also playable in the [i][[Super Smash Bros.]][/i] games, starting with [i]Brawl[/i]. In [i]Brawl[/i] specifically, he is notorious for being a "god tier" character, which was addressed in the later [i]Smash[/i] games.

title: halberd
body:
A popular and versatile [[polearm]]. Its main distinguishing features are a head consisting of an [[axe]] blade, a [[spear]]head, and a hook or angled spike opposite the axe.

While the term halberd refers specifically to the medieval/renaissance European polearm, similar polearms such as the knightly poleaxe/pollaxe and Chinese [[qinglong ji]] also fall under this category.

Not to be confused with [[Meta Knight|Meta Knight's]] [[halberd_(airship)|signature battleship]].

title: saber_lily
body:
A non-canonical alternate costume of [[Saber (fate)|]] playable in the [[Fate/Unlimited Codes]] fighting game for the PS2 based on [[Fate/stay night]]. She also appeared in the Type-Moon OVA [[Carnival Phantasm]], along with [[Phantas-Moon]], [[Magical Amber]], and [[Kaleido Ruby]]. 

She is basically [[Saber (fate)|]] as a [[magical girl]] with a strong [[lily (flower)|lily]] motif, though not in a literal sense.

As of the release of [[Fate/Grand Order]], she has gotten an official story, where she is Saber during her earlier days, still wielding [[Caliburn (fate)|]] and just beginning to walk the path of a king. She was still an inexperienced knight, looked  like an adorable lily, and her eyes brimmed with shining hope. To experience many things, she traveled the land and engaged in many adventures. The people she saved in his time came to call her in past of the Knight Princess, for her brilliance and beauty.

Saber Lily is treated as a separate character from Saber, so do not add the [[Saber (fate)|]] tag if she is by herself. It's only applicable if both characters are together in the image.

title: yakumo_yukari
body:
The "Youkai of Boundaries". Phantasm Stage boss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Perfect Cherry Blossom]] and later a recurring playable character.

A powerful youkai of at least 1200 years of age, reputedly older than [[Gensokyo]] itself. Nominally responsible for guarding the border between Gensokyo and the outside world, but is frequently sleeping or slacking around, leaving her work to her shikigami [[Yakumo Ran]] and Ran's own shikigami [[Chen]].

Yukari has the power to manipulate boundaries, as well as create [[gap (touhou)|]]s, leading to her nickname "Sukima". However, she frequently holds back her powers and most of the time she only goes as far as playfully dragging any unsuspecting human from the outside world into Gensoukyou.

in [[Silent Sinner in Blue]] she has two pet crows - [[Zenki (touhou)|]] and [[Goki (touhou)|]].

Besides her servants, she is friends with [[Ibuki Suika]], [[Saigyouji Yuyuko]] (whom she knew from as early as the latter's days as a human) and [[Hakurei Reimu]] (the other barrier guardian, whom she sometimes pesters). Also hinted to be [[Morichika Rinnosuke]]'s business partner and supplier of items from the outside world. Yukari has an as-yet undefined connection to [[Maribel Hearn]].

title: ingo_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Ingo[/b], known as [b]Nobori[/b] (ノボリ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon bw|Black and White]][/i].

This Subway Boss is the older of the twin brothers who run the Battle Subway in Unova. He usually specializes in Single Battles [tn](official bio)[/tn]. 
[spoilers]He also makes an appearance in [i][[Pokemon Legends: Arceus|Pokémon Legends: Arceus]][/i], having been sent back in time to Hisui like [[akari (pokemon)|the]] [[rei (pokemon)|protagonist]] and suffering from severe amnesia.[/spoilers]

He has [[grey eyes]] and [[short hair|short]] [[grey hair]] with [[long sideburns]]. He wears a [[black headwear|black]] [[peaked cap|cap]], a [[long sleeves|long-sleeve]] [[high collar]] [[black coat|black]] [[trench coat|coat]], a [[collared shirt|collared]] [[white shirt|white]] [[dress shirt|shirt]] with a [[blue necktie|tie]], [[white gloves|gloves]], a [[belt buckle|buckled]] [[brown belt|belt]], and [[black pants]] [[black footwear|and]] [[shoes]].

h4. Official Art
* !post #5196414: [[Pokemon bw|Black/White]]
* !post #5296081: [[Pokemon Legends: Arceus|Legends Arceus]] (Concept Art)

h4. See also

* [b]Relatives[/b]
** [[Emmet (pokemon)|]] (twin brother)
* [b]Voice actor[/b]
** [[Matsuoka Yoshitsugu]]

* "Bulbapedia: Ingo":[https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Ingo]

title: streaked_hair
body:
[[Multicolored hair]] or [[two-tone hair]] where the majority of the hair is one color, while only one or multiple small streaks possess a different color or colors.

The specific standard hair color(s) in the streaks can also be tagged (similar to the" [i]color[/i]_trim":[/wiki_pages?commit=Search&search%5Btitle_normalize%5D=%2A_trim] tags):

title: kieran_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Kieran[/b], known as [b]Suguri[/b] (スグリ) in Japan, is a character from [[Pokemon sv|Pokémon Scarlet and Violet]]'s expansions, "The Teal Mask" and "The Indigo Disk".

He was born in Kitakami and is a student at Blueberry Academy. He is the younger brother of [[carmine (pokemon)|Carmine.]] His signature Pokémon is [[Dipplin]], and later on, [[Hydrapple]].

h4. Official art
